latestPosts.caption: Paying my meta ad bill has to be my least favourite activity ever - the only ‘hack’ that works to profitably grow using performance marketing is making your messaging better and better! You have to problem solve for your customer through both the product but ALSO the communication. Make life easy for them - preempt their problems and solve it in 30 seconds or less. Getting better and better at this is the secret to our growth!

Let’s be real - what’s a vacation without a whole new wardrobe for it? At @uptownie101 we love dressing you for your days off! 

Your vacation capsule wardrobe should have 3 things - a versatile white shirt with some style that you can look cute but still feel comfortable in, an eye-catching midi with some fun like this one with a cute cut out, and a trendy top that you can layer for day or night. 

Coming soon : a surprise launch for all our customers looking to really step up their vacation wardrobe game! Watch this space 👀

latestPosts.caption:
Proudly by Indian women, for Indian women! 🇮🇳 

When we tell people that @uptownie101 has a 90% female team they’re shocked. Shocked that we don’t have men in managerial roles, shocked that all technical roles are capably performed by women employees and that we have no male investors or stakeholders. 

But if we believe ANYTHING, we believe that women can do it all! They can build big businesses, they can negotiate with 3rd parties, they can do product development, set up and run strong ops, have a razor sharp control over their company’s finances and can do it all while still making creative and fun marketing content. 

Our team is our secret sauce, the magic that powers the brand, and while we may change or pivot in many ways we will always stay true to this philosophy- of having an empowered, capable team of power women! 

This women’s day let’s raise a toast to women - who defeat all odds to shine in every space!

Woman’s day is a good time to remind us about the importance of self care. Some self care looks like a night in doing skin care, or reading a good book. My ultimate self care has always been dance. 💃

I learnt kathak since the age of 4, and have always found ultimate peace and relaxation in learning and perfecting a new choreography.

Life as an entrepreneur can be overwhelming - there’s a constant need to be connected and reachable. I always have to be available - on call, email and WhatsApp and never know when the next fire at work will be or what it will be. Often, it can feel like I’m living life on the edge. 

My weekly dance classes are a reminder to focus inwards and to put away my devices. Learning a new dance means focusing on that and only that. For one hour a week my work worries are replaced with concentration on the present. It gives me an opportunity to reconnect with my body and relive a childhood hobby. 

I truly can’t recommend it enough! 
What’s your form of self care - tell me in the comments below!

It doesn’t take 💰 crores of VC funding or fancy stores to build a successful consumer brand. It takes insight 🔍, vision 🚀, and the relentless ability to execute ⚡. Most of all, it takes empathy ❤️—the ability to step into our customers’ shoes 👠 and truly understand their lives.

As a proudly Made in India 🇮🇳 brand, serving lakhs of Indian women, our core strength is creating collections that make their lives easier & more stylish ✨. And that’s the fuel to our rocket ship! 🚀🔥
Running a startup means making it through days that feel like nightmares - but these days leave behind important lessons that become long term building blocks!
Still saying didi on work calls with 10 other people because nothing else sounds right 🤷‍♀️
👭🏻💻 Working with your sister is a wild ride 🌟- some days you’re best friends 🥰🫰🏻, some days you want to kill each other 🤷🏻‍♀️🎯- but it’s always an experience you wouldn’t trade for the world! 🫂🥳😎

2025 is the year we said good bye to the comfort zone - and it was a blast! Still feels unreal that we’ve created all these fun and trendy fits - everytime I wear an Uptownie product I feel lucky and blessed!

Kept it fresh and fun with some 🇰🇷✨ Korean-inspired fashion! A short skirt and white shirt will always give me some 🎒📚 back-to-school nostalgia, and we found this trend totally irresistible! 💖 It’s a sneak peek 👀 and hasn’t launched yet, so watch this space! 🚀🔥
